<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Web on Min Soe Han</title><link>https://minsoehan.com/tags/web/</link><description>Recent content in Web on Min Soe Han</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 03 Oct 2025 10:16:09 +0630</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://minsoehan.com/tags/web/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Image Processing for Website</title><link>https://minsoehan.com/tech/image-processing/</link><pubDate>Fri, 03 Oct 2025 10:16:09 +0630</pubDate><guid>https://minsoehan.com/tech/image-processing/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Image processing became essential part of web development nowadays. It is my way of image processing in &lt;a href="https://archlinux.org/"&gt;Arch Linux&lt;/a&gt; with following steps:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resizing big image before optimizing using &lt;a href="https://imagemagick.org/"&gt;ImageMagic&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href="https://ffmpeg.org/"&gt;FFmpeg&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimizing image using:
&lt;ul class="mb0"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/tjko/jpegoptim"&gt;jpegoptim&lt;/a&gt; for JPG&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://pngquant.org/"&gt;pngquant&lt;/a&gt; for PNG or&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://optipng.sourceforge.net/"&gt;optipng&lt;/a&gt; for PNG or&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/oxipng/oxipng"&gt;oxipng&lt;/a&gt; for PNG or&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://squoosh.app/"&gt;Squoosh&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href="https://github.com/GoogleChromeLabs/squoosh"&gt;Squoosh GitHub&lt;/a&gt; of Google for JPG and PNG&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Convert image to &lt;code&gt;webp&lt;/code&gt; format using &lt;code&gt;cwebp&lt;/code&gt; of &lt;a href="https://github.com/webmproject/libwebp"&gt;libwebp&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h3 class="mt3rem" id="install-required-software-in-arch-linux"&gt;Install Required Software in Arch Linux&lt;/h3&gt;



&lt;div class="code-header"&gt;
 &lt;div class="text"&gt;~&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="copy-code-below"&gt;&lt;i class="fa-solid fa-copy"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 &lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-text" data-lang="text"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pacman -S jpegoptim pngquant libwebp libwebp-utils&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3 class="mt3rem" id="resize-image"&gt;Resize Image&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using &lt;a href="https://imagemagick.org/"&gt;ImageMagic&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>